==Description== <!--T:2-->

<!--T:3-->
The '''Arch ToggleSubs''' tools toggles the visibility of all the subtractions of an [[BIM_Workbench|BIM]] object between visible and hidden.

<!--T:10-->
Normally, if an Arch object, like an [[Arch_Wall|Arch Wall]], is selected and you press {{KEY|Space}} only the external wall will be hidden or made visible, but not the internal objects.

<!--T:11-->
With this tool, the internal subtracted objects will all become visible or hidden.

==Usage== <!--T:4-->

<!--T:5-->
# Select an Arch object that has subtractions.
# Select the {{MenuCommand|Utils → [[Image:Arch_ToggleSubs.svg|16px]] Toggle subcomponents}} option from the menu.

== Options== <!--T:6-->

<!--T:7-->
The color of a subtraction element can follow the style of [[Draft_ToggleConstructionMode|Draft construction]] elements, by activating the appropriate option in the [[Arch_Preferences|Arch Preferences]], in the menu {{MenuCommand|Edit → Preferences → Arch → General settings → Apply Draft construction style to subcomponents}}.

<!--T:12-->
The [[Draft_ToggleConstructionMode|Draft construction]] style can be set in the [[Draft_Preferences|Draft Preferences]], in the menu {{MenuCommand|Preferences → Draft → General Draft}}.


